data.description: Looking for a low mortgage interest rate? Maybe you can assume the Seller's Gov't backed mortgage!   Have you been dreaming about owning a  home in Morris Park?  Two full baths, one on each floor, adds convenience and accessibility for the residents. The accessible rear lane is a practical feature that allows for easy car access, making loading and unloading hassle-free. Additionally, it provides a space for backyard parties and furniture deliveries.  The proximity to Morris Park offers the opportunity for enjoyable activities such as BBQs, neighborhood gardening, and sports events, fostering a sense of community. The location's convenience is further highlighted by its proximity to City Avenue, I-76, and other points beyond, making commuting and travel more accessible.  The large bedrooms with ample closet space provide comfort and storage options. The kitchen, with its abundance of cabinets, presents an opportunity for customization and personalization. The full-height walkout basement with daylight is a versatile space that can be utilized for various purposes, such as storage or as an additional living area. The presence of a storage room under the porch and a mechanical room at the back of the basement further enhance the house's practicality and organization.  With the potential for customization and the convenient features it offers, this Large Morris Park home holds promise for its future owners to create a comfortable and enjoyable living space.  This home will need substantial work. No repairs by the Seller will be made.  This home may qualify for a $10,000 homebuyer grant.  Schedule your showing today with a licensed Real Estate Agent!
